---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Parcel Delivery and No One at Home: What to Do? - parcelLab"
  description="A guide to alternative parcel delivery options when no one is home, from personal parcel boxes to packstations and trunk delivery."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Research</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Parcel Delivery and No One at Home -- What to Do?</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2019-08-29">August 29, 2019</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>5 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          When anticipated packages arrive while you're away, delivery services offer multiple alternatives to ensure safe parcel receipt. Here's a comprehensive guide to the options available.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">1. Personal Parcel Boxes</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Customers install boxes at their residences that delivery personnel can access via key chip or smartphone application. This system supports returns as well, allowing carriers to collect pre-franked items.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">2. Neighbor Delivery</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Parcels can be left with neighboring residents. Some carriers permit customers to designate preferred neighbors. However, customers may face delays locating neighbors and retrieving packages.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">3. Drop-off Permissions</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Customers authorize specific locations -- garages, porches, or other safe spots -- for parcel placement without signatures. The customer assumes liability for theft or damage at the designated site.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">4. Packstations</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Automated locker facilities allow delivery to secure stations. Customers register and select their preferred station, receiving notifications upon deposit. This free service operates around the clock.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">5. Post Office and Parcel Shops</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Branches and shops offer seven-day pickup windows. Customers present identification documents, and proxy authorization enables others to retrieve parcels on their behalf.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">6. Trunk Delivery</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Partnerships with vehicle manufacturers permit parcel placement in car trunks via app coordination. Adoption remains limited -- only 2% of German respondents use this service -- but it represents an innovative alternative.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">7. Multi-Family Parcel Boxes</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Apartment buildings install compartmentalized boxes allowing carriers to deposit multiple parcels securely, making delivery convenient for all residents.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Key Statistic</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--ink)]">53 of 100 retailers observed do not communicate with customers during shipping, while only 15 engage in direct communication rather than delegating to logistics providers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Regardless of which delivery alternative customers choose, retailers should prioritize proactive shipping communication through branded tracking pages and personalized notifications. Keeping customers informed reduces failed deliveries and builds a stronger post-purchase experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
